data.name: label1.Text
data.value:
PinVol makes it easier to control the audio volume in your pin cab. Leave PinVol running in the background. The program will intercept the "hot keys" assigned below, even when other applications are running. Assign keys corresponding to buttons on your cabinet so that you can adjust the volume via the cabinet buttons during play.
You can minimize this window if you wish, to get it out of the way while running other programs.

data.name: label12.Text
data.value: By default, system volume changes you make through other programs (such as the task bar volume controls) apply to the "Global" volume level, so they'll affect the volume for all pinball tables and other programs, proportionaly to the saved settings for each table. If you check this box, external changes will apply to the current table only.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: Table volume keys: These keys adjust the volume for the CURRENT table/program only. PinVol remembers the individual level for each context, and switches back to the saved level each time you return to a table or app. The context volume is remembered as a percentage of the Global level, so changes to the global level will be applied proportionally to all tables and apps.

data.name: label21.Text
data.value: SSF volume keys: These keys adjust the volume/gain for the CURRENT table/program only and work in the same way as the table keys. It is easier if you use the same keys as you have set for your table and additionally use Ctrl, Alt, Shift or Win keys.

data.name: label19.Text
data.value: Check this box if you want to set the per-table volume level independently for secondary audio devices. This will let you map an additional pair of keys to control the per-table volume for secondary devices.
